:"Transfer frozen gelato mixture into refrigerator for 15 minutes to soften slightly, then cut into pieces (4 x 4 cm). Place half of the gelato pieces into mixing bowl and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b> with aid of spatula. Transfer into a freezable storage container."},{"content":"Place remaining half of the gelato pieces into mixing bowl and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b> with aid of spatula. Transfer into freezable container with gelato and return to freezer for a minimum of 2 hours. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Peanut bark"},{"content":"Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place peanuts into mixing bowl and crush <b>8 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Melt <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Spread melted chocolate out thinly onto prepared baking tray. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the reserved crushed peanuts. Place into refrigerator to set (approx. 10 minutes)."},{"content":"Break bark into shards. Serve gelato with bark and sprinkle with remaining crushed peanuts."}],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","28h","6 portions"]}